# Your rule content

A description of how resources (articles, artwork, blogs, collections, users, comments.) are interrelated through fields that reference other collections, and how these relationships can be populated. In other words, how our data model is structured and how relationships between entities are established in our MongoDB schema.

- Article: References a User (author) and an Artwork.
- Artwork: Belongs to one or more Collections; referenced by Users via Watchlists and Favourites.
- Blog: References a User (author) and contains Comments.
- Comment: References a User (author) and links to a Blog.
- Collection: Contains multiple Artworks.
- User: Associated with comments (Comment), a watchlist (Artwork), and favourites (Artwork).